###What is git?

Git is a [version control system](http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-About-Version-Control) that keeps track of changes to files, so that you can have a history of all the changes made to a file and you can revert to a specific version later on. Here are some features of Git:

* Keep separate branches of development
* Rollback to a previous version if a bug was found
* Different versions for development and deployment; the deployment version should be a stable one
* Merging branches into one branch
* ...

Here is a free online book if you want to learn more about Git: [Pro Git](http://git-scm.com/book).
